This paper deals with the application of deep learning methods for cell detection in histology images, which is a common problem in computer vision and image analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach based on deconvolution, which involves modifying a convolutional neural network (CNN) to generate points as cell detection. This approach involves training the CNN for mapped labels, which is a common technique in machine learning and artificial intelligence, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also involves some optimization and tuning of the CNN, which is a common topic in information retrieval and optimization, suggesting that cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image analysis and processing, which is a common topic in multimedia and computer graphics, suggesting that cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible sub-category.
